[{"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-06-25T23:30:17+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"A boy in a checkered red and white tablecloth of a shirt, with red hair, generated by OpenAI, to represent Toys R Us founder Charles Lazarus.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/fmX2JU7vRY9I_6qhe5sqOjT_hP4=/0x0:1620x1080/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73427804/vlcsnap_2024_06_25_16h06m34s808.0.png\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Toys R Us</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"9G0DXS\">Do you have fond memories of Toys \u201cR\u201d Us, back <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/23758492/private-equity-brendan-ballou-plunder-finance-doj\">before private equity helped lay it to waste</a>? If so, I\u2019m really curious what you think of <a href=\"https://go.redirectingat.com?id=66960X1514734&amp;xs=1&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.toysrus.com%2Fpages%2Fstudios&amp;referrer=theverge.com&amp;sref=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theverge.com%2F2024%2F6%2F25%2F24186051%2Ftoys-r-us-openai-sora-brand-film\" rel=\"sponsored nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\">this partially AI-generated vide", "id": 767169, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/6/25/24186051/toys-r-us-openai-sora-brand-film", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 86, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "The owner of Toys \u2018R\u2019 Us just used OpenAI\u2019s Sora to animate the zombie brand", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-06-25T23:00:00+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Graphic showing a v-shaped illustration with sparkle icons indicating AI.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/XaiXGVT941Nm0WcXreRcCxLtxFw=/0x71:1692x1199/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73427760/Static_Official_Release__Horizontal_16x9__2560x1440_crop.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>In case you were wondering, yes, there will be lots of AI.</em> | Image: Samsung</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"z9BXVK\">Samsung\u2019s next Unpacked summer launch event will take place on July 10th in Paris, France, the company <a href=\"https://news.samsung.com/us/samsung-galaxy-unpacked-july-2024-galaxy-ai-is-here-invitation-livestream-replay/\">announced on Tuesday</a>. The animation accompanying the invitation hints at foldables, and the invite itself removes all doubt: \u201cPrepare to discover the power of Galaxy AI, now infused into the latest Galaxy Z series and the entire Galaxy ecosystem.\u201d But we\u2019re also on the lookout for something of a different shape:", "id": 767170, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/6/25/24178801/samsung-unpacked-summer-2024-galaxy-z-fold-6-ring", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 86, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Samsung just announced a date for its next Unpacked", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-06-25T22:40:31+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Vector illustration of the Chat GPT logo.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/p4UMioTA9xpbZ9Is_w-LxRjaNfY=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73427738/STK155_OPEN_AI_CVirginia_C.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"QyWhJZ\">The advanced voice mode for ChatGPT that <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/5/20/24161253/scarlett-johansson-openai-altman-legal-action\">sparked a tussle with Scarlett Johansson</a> was an important element of OpenAI\u2019s Spring Update event, where it also revealed <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/5/13/24155573/chatgpt-app-desktop-mac\">a desktop app for ChatGPT</a>.</p>\n<p id=\"dg93TU\">Now, OpenAI says it will \u201cneed one more month to reach our bar to launch\u201d an alpha version of <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/5/13/24155652/chatgpt-voice-mode-gpt4o-upgrades\">the new voice mode</a> to a small group of ChatGPT Plus subscribers, with plans to allow acces", "id": 766871, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/6/25/24186032/openai-chatgpt-mac-app-advanced-voice-mode-delayed", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 86, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "ChatGPT\u2019s Mac app is here, but its flirty advanced voice mode has been delayed", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-06-25T22:04:01+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"An in-game McLaren Senna supercar from the game Forza Horizon 4.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/L_zAvMFGq-lTYkevhQydrPBN7f4=/300x0:3540x2160/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73427620/edecbd5e_4a92_4811_8a84_0fdc6e4baae3.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Xbox Game Studios / Turn 10</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"9mYCwe\">The \u201c<a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/1/30/24055807/spec-ops-the-line-delisting-licensing-2k\">delisting</a>\u201d ax is swinging <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/3/8/24094536/adult-swim-games-delisted-warner-bros-discovery\">once again</a>, and this time, <em>Forza Horizon 4</em> is the latest major video game to be cleaved from digital storefronts. Developer Playground Games <a href=\"https://forza.net/news/forza-horizon-4-delisting\">announced on its site</a> that sales of the 2018 open-world racer are ending due to licensing and partner agreements, and the game will be removed from Microsoft stores and S", "id": 766872, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/6/25/24185972/forza-horizon-4-xbox-pc-microsoft-steam-delisted", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 86, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Forza Horizon 4 will be delisted from Microsoft stores and Steam in December", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-06-25T21:20:04+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"A gamer holding the 8BitDo Ultimate 2C Wireless Controller in front of a laptop computer.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/tao_mRl1UhcjOnXNN60DMiP2XXY=/0x0:1251x834/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73427527/8bitdo_Ultimate_2C_Wireless_Controller1.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>The new 8BitDo Ultimate 2C Wireless Controller includes Bluetooth, USB-C, and 2.4GHz connectivity.</em> | Image: 8BitDo</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"cJ8NV0\">8BitDo announced its <a href=\"https://www.8bitdo.com/ultimate-2c-wireless-controller/\">latest budget-minded wireless controller</a> today, the Ultimate 2C. For $29.99, it includes features like an extra pair of shoulder buttons to satisfy most PC and Android gamers, Hall effect sticks and triggers to keep problems like the Switch\u2019s <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/21504741/nintendo-switch-joy-con-drift-problem-explained\">notorious \u201cJoy-Con drift\u201d</a> at bay, and three different ways to connect it t", "id": 765990, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/6/25/24185806/gaming-8bitdo-controller-ultimate-2c-hall-effect", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 86, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "8BitDo\u2019s $29.99 Ultimate 2C controller adds two more shoulder buttons", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-06-25T20:20:52+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/h3UAdMk7pAvxTizmFUncXHIqJJQ=/0x1:3000x2001/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73427326/07_Rivian_R2.5.jpg\" />\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"ue2bWZ\">Volkswagen is investing $1 billion in Rivian as part of a new joint venture that will give the German auto giant access to the buzzy California EV company\u2019s software and EV platform. Rivian will receive an additional $4 billion over time, for a total sum of $5 billion. </p>\n<p id=\"Tlpb61\">The joint venture will be co-owned by Rivian and VW Group, which oversees brands like Audi, Porsche, Lamborghini, and its flagship Volkswagen. The two companies will introduce vehicles developed from the joint venture in the \u201csecond half of the decade,\u201d they announced.</p>\n<p id=\"K9vuTJ\">The new venture was announced in <a href=\"https://x.com/RJScaringe/status/1805694762286301406\">a post from Rivian CEO RJ Scaringe</a>, who noted the investment will help the company bring its next ", "id": 765991, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/6/25/24185946/vw-rivian-joint-venture-investment-software-r2", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 86, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "VW will invest up to $5 billion in Rivian as part of new EV joint venture", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-06-25T19:24:38+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/WLF0KQ0GvR1uKEA7U3hbXaCAZ-4=/0x640:3840x3200/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73427193/Ceiling_White_Clouds_FinalRender_V1C.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>The Lifx ceiling light features full-color, tunable white light and an array of effects to light up your home.</em> | Image: Lifx</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"NcbDdp\">Smart light fixtures are quickly becoming a thing, making it a little easier to add colorful, fun, and useful lighting effects to more areas of your home than you traditionally can with <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/23156554/smart-bulbs-switch-lighting-guide-how-to\">smart light bulbs</a>. While these types of fixtures have been quite pricey, smart lighting company Lifx just announced its <a href=\"https://www.lifx.com/products/ceiling-light-15-black-trim\">new Super Color Ceiling Light</a> starting at just $89.97. </p>\n<div class=\"c-float-left c-float-hang\"><aside id=\"XjZM17", "id": 765992, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/6/25/24185684/lifx-super-color-ceiling-light-matter-price-specs", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 86, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "This Matter-enabled smart ceiling light costs under $100", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-06-25T19:17:53+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Deadmau5 Announces New Collection Of Music \u201cmau5ville: level 1\u201d\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/QqZZUN8qoNeQRM5PcjkJPRcI8NQ=/387x17:2364x1335/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73427183/998090246.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Photo by Michael Tullberg / Getty Images</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p>Years after Twitch\u2019s ban, the streamer confirms it was due to messages he sent to a minor on the platform.</p>\n  <p>\n    <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/24185864/dr-disrespect-twitch-ban\">Continue reading&hellip;</a>\n  </p>", "id": 765993, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/24185864/dr-disrespect-twitch-ban", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 86, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Dr Disrespect\u2019s Twitch ban, explained", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-06-25T19:00:00+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"The back of the Xreal Beam Pro, a chunky white Android tablet.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/E21DRI27rurDQDY1xMNsQjl-vhE=/0x168:4032x2856/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73427131/20240619_132925.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>An Android phone minus the phone plus two giant cameras.</em> | Image: Adi Robertson / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"bg8WwC\">Xreal is one of the few companies trying to sell mass-market augmented reality headsets without an existing big tech empire. But its latest product isn\u2019t a pair of glasses; it\u2019s a <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/6/18/24180298/xreal-beam-pro-ar-glasses-usb-c-launch\">phone-sized Android tablet designed to keep you using them</a>. At last week\u2019s Augmented World Expo (AWE) the company announced the Beam Pro, a combination battery, app repository, and 3D video recorder. It\u2019s a pragmatic solution to a very obvious problem \u2014 even if, at first glance, I wish it were wei", "id": 765994, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/24185094/xreal-beam-pro-awe-ar-tablet-hands-on", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 86, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "This tiny tablet is a smart upgrade for AR glasses", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-06-25T18:33:11+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Pittsburgh Pirates v San Diego Padres\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/65-UvBTnNg2Y43Pk7SmqkIOjO-w=/0x0:4125x2750/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73427086/1555295895.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Photo by Matt Thomas / San Diego Padres / Getty Images</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"oGs1e4\">Guy Beahm, better known by his streamer persona Dr Disrespect, said he was banned from Twitch <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2020/6/26/21304907/dr-disrespect-twitch-ban-no-reason-given\">four years ago</a> due to private messages he sent to a minor that \u201csometimes leaned too much in the direction of being inappropriate.\u201d</p>\n<p id=\"WRSx7n\">Beahm shared details of the ban in <a href=\"https://x.com/DrDisrespect/status/1805668256088572089\">a lengthy post to X</a>, marking the first time he\u2019s directly addressed the reason for his removal.</p>\n<p id=\"aR18dE\">\u201cEveryone has been wanting to know why I was banned from Twitch, but for reasons outside of", "id": 765995, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/6/25/24185821/dr-disrespect-twitch-ban-explanation-inappropriate-messages", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 86, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Dr Disrespect finally shares why he was banned from Twitch", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-06-25T18:19:38+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Epomaker TH80 keyboard on a desk.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/1DA4wASAJWYXrPvVHgO54AngCNs=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73427050/226317_Mechanical_Keyboard_Buying_Guide_JPorter_0005.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Jon Porter / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"qxcRav\">With RGB lighting and customizability, most mechanical keyboards are way more fun to type on than your regular old keyboard. Those perks typically come at a cost, though \u2014 but not as much today because <strong>Epomaker\u2019s TH80 Pro</strong> is on sale at <a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/EPOMAKER-Bluetooth-Mechanical-Keyboard-Capacity/dp/B0BMKBMCS2?tag=theverge02-20\" rel=\"sponsored nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Amazon</a> for $62.99 ($27 off). That\u2019s a new all-time low price on the TH80 Pro and is available on keyboards with Gateron switches in select colors \u2014 including black, red, and yellow \u2014 as well as with Budgerigar switches.<", "id": 765996, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/6/25/24185762/amazon-epomaker-th80-pro-deal-sale", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 86, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Epomaker\u2019s TH80 Pro, one of our top mechanical keyboard picks, is at its best price", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-06-25T18:04:57+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Google logo with colorful shapes\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/g5ZxE9TI9Jb76L8V4NNIWzHYL-A=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73427032/STK093_Google_04.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Illustration: The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"jIZvq8\">The latest feature <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2019/11/26/20977968/google-graveyard-products-shut-down-dead-not-supported-discontinues-spring-cleaning\">headed to the Google graveyard</a> is continuous scrolling on search results, according to a <a href=\"https://searchengineland.com/google-dropping-continuous-scroll-in-search-results-443529\">report from <em>Search Engine Land</em></a>. The user experience, which mirrored the endless scrolling behavior of social media feeds, was originally <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2021/10/14/22726625/google-search-results-continuous-scrolling-mobile-doomscroll\">introduced for search results on mobile devices</a> in October of 20", "id": 765997, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/6/25/24185727/google-search-continuous-scrolling-doomscrolling-graveyard", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 86, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Google is killing infinite scroll on search results", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-06-25T17:00:00+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"An image of a prototype projector that reflects glasses-free 3D onto a car\u2019s windshield.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/VIUa9qWEUnz2wkP8WxwOs1e7Z9g=/0x168:4032x2856/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73426858/20240618_163130.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>A huge panel becomes an AR projector powered by data from eye tracking sensors in this prototype.</em> | Image: Adi Robertson / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"UmJaEs\">Car infotainment systems are getting ever bigger, but a startup\u2019s new prototype takes things further than even something like Ford\u2019s <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/1/22/24045932/ford-android-screen-display-size-os-apps-gaming-lincoln\">pillar-to-pillar touchscreen</a> \u2014 by turning your windshield into a full-color 3D heads-up display.</p>\n<p id=\"dwc8cJ\">Distance Technologies, established by the co-founders of enterprise headset maker Varjo, showed off its design last week at Augmented World Expo ", "id": 762965, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/24185134/distance-technologies-car-hud-prototype-awe-hands-on", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 86, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "This prototype turns your car\u2019s windshield into a giant AR display", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-06-25T16:56:28+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Four people wearing matching uniforms stand around a large capsule that recently landed on Earth. A Chinese flag stands next to them.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/E1Y7G5hGPPpBKTuFZmThvfL_m1I=/0x0:6240x4160/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73426854/2159172284.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>The return capsule of the Chang\u2019e 6 probe lands at the designated landi